Please note that the values for test_url are based on a standard Django development server URL. If running on a different environment, you may need to adjust accordingly.

For example:
- The Development Server: http://localhost:8000/
- Production (Gunicorn/Nginx): https://example.com/
- Production (Gunicorn/Apache):

    - ServerName example.com
    - DocumentRoot /path/to/your/project/public
    - RewriteEngine On
    - RewriteCond %{REQUEST_URI} !^/media/
    - RewriteRule ^(.*)$ wsgi.py [QSA,L]
And the test_url in your button to "HelloWorld" page should be set to: http://localhost:8000/helloworld/

Also, remember that for displaying 'Hello World' message you do not need any parameter.
